A construction site collapsed killing one person on the Nico
Smith Street in Rietfontein Pretoria on Thursday morning. Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said reports from the
scene indicated that workers had been pouring cement on the top floor gave way. ALSO READ: SANDF MEMBER BUST FOR ROBBERY! “Medics assessed the scene and found that four adult males
had sustained moderate injuries and were treated on scene before being
transported by private ambulance to a hospital for further treatment. “Another adult male believed to be in his late thirties
sustained fatal injuries in the collapse and was declared deceased on the
scene,” Herbst said. He said the scene had been cordoned off for investigations
to take place.